    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 70ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [95ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the meatballs are browned, transfer them to a plate and return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
